Given an array of numbers, sort the array in ascending order.
Given an array of numbers, find the smallest and largest elements in the array.
Given an array of numbers, find the median of the array.
Given an array of numbers, find the kth smallest element in the array.
Given an array of numbers, find the number of times each element appears in the array.
Given an array of numbers, find the sum of all the elements in the array.
Given an array of numbers, find the product of all the elements in the array.
Given an array of numbers, find the difference between the largest and smallest elements in the array.
Given an array of numbers, find the average of all the elements in the array.
Given an array of numbers, find the standard deviation of all the elements in the array.
In addition to these problems, merge sort can also be used to solve many other problems, such as:

Merging two sorted arrays.
Splitting an array into two sorted arrays.
Finding the intersection of two sorted arrays.
Finding the union of two sorted arrays.
Finding the difference of two sorted arrays.
Counting the number of inversions in an array.
Sorting an array of strings.
Sorting an array of objects.
Merge sort is a very versatile sorting algorithm that can be used to solve a wide variety of problem